      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "For those stubborn, deep-set particles, a small, stiff detail brush is your best tool. You can use this brush to meticulously sweep out the corners and the deepest crevices where the tape will sit. If you have a can of compressed air, a very short, controlled blast can also help blow out finer dust, but be careful not to blow the surrounding drywall dust into the seam itself. This meticulous cleaning prevents those tiny imperfections from popping through your final paint coat.",
